  "number": "2.3.8",
  "title": "",
  "body": " Based on data from the FDA the average amount of mercury found in fresh or frozen salmon is 0.022 ppm (parts per million). This means there are 0.022 mg of mercury in one liter of salmon. If a meal portion of salmon is 0.0020 liters how much mercury is consumed?  We can use the ratio . We apply this ratio to the given volume of 0.0020 liters.   "
